                <div class="faq-q">What is insider buying and why does it matter?</div>
                <div class="faq-a">Insider buying occurs when officers, directors, or key executives purchase stock in their own company on the open market. Legendary investor Peter Lynch famously noted that while insiders might sell their stock for many reasons, they usually only buy it for one: they think the price is going to go up.</div>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-item">
                <div class="faq-q">What is an SEC Form 4 filing?</div>
